DoS / DDoS does not refer to a technique or method of transport . It ' s largely defined by intention + end result . This is not rocket surgery .

Listening to @twoscooters talk about how harassment is important . And how we are going to help you through it .
I am bringing it up for one reason . GamerGate has brought harassment into the limelight , but rest assured , it ' s always there .
This is a problem that affects everyone , but we have seen far more harassment targeting women .
It is fitting that we are now seeing these strong women speaking out and trying to fix problems that others are uncertain of how to tackle .
Oh gosh she mentioned me and gg autoblocker in her talk and now I am blushing and trying not to sniffle .
In this ongoing tragedy , we found our voices & each other . We have learned to work together , and to support & encourage these amazing women .
I can not even find the words to describe how much I value the work of all the people I have met during this time . How much I love all of them .
We talk about GamerGate a lot . But the truth is , GamerGate is not the real battle . It ' s a symptom of a larger problem .
Online harassment is something most people have faced at some point , regardless of their views on ethics in games journalism .
It ' s a really tough problem , because it ' s a BIG problem . It is far reaching . It has many different forms .
The scope of the problem can discourage people from trying to fight it . Often this leads to thinking , what can I do ? I am just one person .
You are not just one person . There are many of us , and we all have voices . But more than that , we have resources , experience , and passion .
You are not alone in this . You are never alone in this .
We have seen so many fantastic things happen out of this tragedy . First , we have @femfreq . Amazing advocacy . A voice that is far reaching .
We have @crashoverridenw , an invaluable resource that provides emotional support for targets of harassment .
Both of these organizations have been created to address different aspects of very real problems that affect all of us .
It ' s almost time . <happy>

OAPI will be partnering with @crashoverridenw to provide them with the tools they need .
We are creating tools and resources for individuals . We are working directly with companies on developer policies to make this a reality .
We know what online abuse looks like . We have been studying it , and we will create reports and publish our findings .

Creating a reporting system is difficult , because of the human intervention and level of bias that is involved .
For more egregious cases for harassment , we definitely need to be able to respond to those appropriately . But most toxicity is not this .
Having a high level of toxicity in your community can lead to more serious cases of harassment and abuse , so we need to tackle this head on .
Putting the tools into the hands of users is a GREAT idea . We need more active solutions for protecting ourselves .
